description:
## Проблема

### Qdrant filter НЕ поддерживает glob
- Только exact match, substring (text), match any
- Нет regex, нет wildcard, нет glob
- `**/workflow/**` не работает

### search_code
- pathPattern конвертируется в regex → Qdrant text match
- Работает нестабильно (text match ≠ regex)

### semantic_search
- pathPattern отсутствует
- Агент не может фильтровать по домену: `**/workflow/**`

## Use Case

Поиск по домену — найти все файлы домена workflow:
- `models/workflow/*`
- `services/workflow/*`  
- `controllers/workflow/*`

**Нужен паттерн:** `**/workflow/**`

## Решение: pathPattern с клиентской фильтрацией

### Архитектура

```
src/qdrant/
├── client.ts              # существующий QdrantManager
├── filters/
│   ├── index.ts           # public API (re-exports)
│   └── glob.ts            # glob matching logic
```

**Принципы:**
- DRY — один модуль для всех MCP tools
- Модульность — изолирован в домене Qdrant
- Без зависимостей от других модулей проекта

### API (функциональный подход)

```typescript
// src/qdrant/filters/glob.ts
import picomatch from 'picomatch';

/**
 * Creates a matcher function for glob pattern
 */
export function createGlobMatcher(pattern: string): (path: string) => boolean {
  return picomatch(pattern, { bash: true });
}

/**
 * Filters search results by glob pattern on relativePath
 * Used for post-filtering Qdrant results when glob not supported natively
 */
export function filterResultsByGlob<T extends { payload?: { relativePath?: string } }>(
  results: T[],
  pattern: string,
): T[] {
  const isMatch = createGlobMatcher(pattern);
  return results.filter(item => {
    const path = item.payload?.relativePath;
    return path && isMatch(path);
  });
}

// src/qdrant/filters/index.ts
export { createGlobMatcher, filterResultsByGlob } from './glob.js';
```

### Интерфейс MCP tools (одинаковый)

```typescript
pathPattern?: string  // Glob pattern: "**/workflow/**", "src/**/*.ts"
```

### semantic_search — добавить pathPattern

```typescript
// schema
{
  collection: string,
  query: string,
  limit?: number,
  filter?: Record<string, any>,  // raw Qdrant filter (без изменений)
  pathPattern?: string,          // NEW: glob фильтрация на клиенте
}

// implementation
import { filterResultsByGlob } from '../qdrant/filters/index.js';

const fetchLimit = pathPattern ? (limit || 5) * 3 : (limit || 5);
const results = await qdrant.search(collection, embedding, fetchLimit, filter);
const filtered = pathPattern 
  ? filterResultsByGlob(results, pathPattern)
  : results;
return filtered.slice(0, limit || 5);
```

### search_code — исправить pathPattern

```typescript
// Убрать glob→regex конвертацию
// Использовать filterResultsByGlob

import { filterResultsByGlob } from '../qdrant/filters/index.js';

const fetchLimit = pathPattern ? limit * 3 : limit;
const results = await qdrant.search(...);  // без path filter в Qdrant
const filtered = pathPattern
  ? filterResultsByGlob(results, pathPattern)
  : results;
return filtered.slice(0, limit);
```

## Примеры использования

```typescript
// Найти всё по домену workflow
pathPattern: "**/workflow/**"

// Только TypeScript в src
pathPattern: "src/**/*.ts"

// Несколько папок (brace expansion)
pathPattern: "{models,services}/workflow/**"
```

## Файлы

### Новые
- src/qdrant/filters/index.ts
- src/qdrant/filters/glob.ts

### Изменения
- package.json — добавить picomatch, @types/picomatch
- src/code/indexer.ts — убрать glob→regex, использовать filterResultsByGlob
- src/tools/schemas.ts — добавить pathPattern в SemanticSearchSchema
- src/tools/search.ts — применить filterResultsByGlob

## Goal
Make search available quickly, enrich metadata in background.

## Architecture
```
Phase 1 (blocking, fast):
├── Tree-sitter parse + chunk
├── Complexity (same AST pass)
├── Collect imports
├── Batch embeddings
├── Upsert to Qdrant
└── → SEARCHABLE

Phase 2 (background worker):
├── Bulk git log → churn map
├── Invert imports → importedBy
├── Qdrant payload updates
└── Cache for next run
```

## Implementation
```typescript
async function indexCodebase(path: string) {
  // Phase 1
  const chunks = await parseAndChunk(path);
  await generateEmbeddings(chunks);
  await upsertToQdrant(chunks);

  console.log('✓ Searchable');

  // Phase 2 (non-blocking)
  setImmediate(async () => {
    const gitData = await collectGitData(path);
    const depGraph = buildDependencyGraph(chunks);
    await enrichPayloads(gitData, depGraph);
    console.log('✓ Enrichment complete');
  });
}
```

## API Changes
- Add `enrichmentStatus` to index_codebase response
- Add `get_enrichment_status` tool

## Goal
Calculate cyclomatic and cognitive complexity from existing AST.

## Implementation
```typescript
function calculateComplexity(node: SyntaxNode): { cyclomatic: number; cognitive: number } {
  let cyclomatic = 1;
  let cognitive = 0;
  let nestingLevel = 0;

  const branchTypes = ['if_statement', 'for_statement', 'while_statement', 
                       'switch_case', 'catch_clause', 'conditional_expression'];

  function traverse(n: SyntaxNode, depth: number) {
    if (branchTypes.includes(n.type)) {
      cyclomatic++;
      cognitive += 1 + depth; // nesting penalty
    }
    for (const child of n.children) {
      traverse(child, depth + (isNestingNode(n) ? 1 : 0));
    }
  }

  traverse(node, 0);
  return { cyclomatic, cognitive };
}
```

## Schema Changes
- Add `complexity.cyclomatic: number`
- Add `complexity.cognitive: number`

## Estimated Cost
- ~0.1-0.2ms per chunk (reuses existing AST)
- Essentially free

## Goal
Track reverse dependencies (who imports this file) for true blast radius.

## Implementation
```typescript
// After all files processed
const importedBy = new Map<string, string[]>();

for (const [file, imports] of allImports) {
  for (const imp of imports) {
    const resolved = resolveImportPath(imp, file);
    if (resolved) {
      if (!importedBy.has(resolved)) importedBy.set(resolved, []);
      importedBy.get(resolved).push(file);
    }
  }
}

// Update Qdrant payloads
```

## Import Resolution
- Relative: ./utils → src/utils.ts or src/utils/index.ts
- Aliases: @/ → tsconfig.paths resolution
- External: ignore (node_modules)

## Schema Changes
- Add `importedBy: string[]` to payload
- Add `importedByCount: number` for easy filtering

## Estimated Cost
- MVP (relative only): 2-3 hours, ~70% coverage
- Full (with aliases): 1-2 days, ~95% coverage

## Goal
Replace inaccurate blame-based commitCount with true churn from git log.

## Implementation
```typescript
// Single bulk call
const log = execSync('git log --all --numstat --format="%H|%an|%ae|%at"');

// Parse into map
const fileChurn: Map<string, number> = parseGitLog(log);

// Add to chunk metadata
metadata.fileChurnCount = fileChurn.get(relativePath) ?? 0;
```

## Schema Changes
- Add `fileChurnCount: number` to payload
- Keep `commitCount` for backwards compatibility (deprecate later)

## Estimated Cost
- +100ms per 1000 files
- File-level granularity (chunks inherit)

express lib/application.js:471-482 имеет:
  methods.forEach(function(method) {
    app[method] = function(path) { ... }
  })
который создаёт app.get, app.post, app.put, app.delete, app.patch, app.options, app.head — 9 HTTP-методов. Walker не извлекает потому что obj[computedKey] LHS subscript_expression, не member_expression. Best-effort heuristic: если subscript_expression в forEach callback, parameter — обычная переменная, можно проследить за инициализатором forEach (methods массив) и эмиттить все статические имена. Сложно, отдельный бед. Низкий приоритет — реальное использование express.get() через JS клиент unresolved будет нечасто.

## Goal
Utilize multi-core for CPU-bound operations.

## Worker Pools
```typescript
import { Worker } from 'worker_threads';

// CPU-bound: parsing, complexity
const cpuPool = new WorkerPool({
  size: os.cpus().length,
  worker: './workers/parse-worker.js'
});

// I/O-bound: git, network
const ioPool = new WorkerPool({
  size: 4,
  worker: './workers/io-worker.js'
});
```

## Pipeline
```typescript
const results = await pipeline(files)
  .parallel(cpuPool, parseAndAnalyze)  // parallel parsing
  .batch(100)                           // batch for API
  .sequential(generateEmbeddings)       // batched API (already optimized)
  .parallel(ioPool, upsertBatch);       // parallel Qdrant writes
```

## Expected Speedup
- 2-4x on typical 4-8 core machines
- Linear scaling with core count for parse phase

## Goal
Cache git analysis results for fast incremental updates.

## Cache Structure
```typescript
interface GitCache {
  version: number;
  headCommit: string;
  indexedAt: number;
  fileChurn: Record<string, number>;
  blameData: Record<string, BlameResult>;
  dependencyGraph: {
    imports: Record<string, string[]>;
    importedBy: Record<string, string[]>;
  };
}
```

## Cache Location
```
.tea-rags/
├── cache/
│   └── <collection-hash>.json
└── config.json
```

## Invalidation Strategy
```typescript
if (cache.headCommit !== currentHead) {
  const changedFiles = getChangedFiles(cache.headCommit, currentHead);
  // Only reprocess changed files
  // Update affected dependency graph nodes
}
```

## Expected Speedup
- No changes: 10-100x faster (just verify HEAD)
- Few changes: 5-20x faster (incremental)

## Goal
On-demand git data fetching when rerank preset needs it but data is missing.

## Use Cases (Fallback)
- Background enrichment not yet completed
- Enrichment failed for some files
- Minimal storage mode (don't pre-compute unused metrics)

## Implementation
```typescript
async function rerank(results: SearchResult[], preset: string) {
  const needsGitData = ['techDebt', 'hotspots', 'codeReview', 'ownership'].includes(preset);
  const needsImportedBy = preset === 'impactAnalysis';

  // Check if enrichment data exists
  const missingGit = needsGitData && results.some(r => \!r.payload.fileChurnCount);
  const missingDeps = needsImportedBy && results.some(r => \!r.payload.importedBy);

  if (missingGit || missingDeps) {
    // On-demand enrichment for these specific files
    const filesToEnrich = results
      .filter(r => \!r.payload.fileChurnCount || \!r.payload.importedBy)
      .map(r => r.payload.relativePath);

    await enrichFiles(filesToEnrich, { git: missingGit, deps: missingDeps });

    // Re-fetch results with enriched data
    return refetchAndRerank(results, preset);
  }

  return applyRerank(results, preset);
}
```

## Notes
- Low priority - two-phase indexing covers 95% of cases
- Adds latency to first query if data missing (~200-500ms)
- Consider caching enriched data for subsequent queries

## Not blocking main roadmap - future optimization only
